entries.femaleVariant: There's still nothing like a good dermal weave. Those polymer networks don't burn so easy.
Me, I don't trust those acidometers. I've seen enough people swap faces after a little drizzle.
Well, the car's still got a shine to it. And that phenolograph's calm as I've ever seen it.
I think we got a shower the other day. You're sure it wasn't the acid kind?
Not too much acid rain lately.
